If you are reading this, well done.
You can share large files with your friends using Sunfire

#################################################
To copy files from your computer to this location:

    scp <path to your file> <your unixid>@sunfire.comp.nus.edu.sg:/tmp/temp/.
Eg.
    scp README.txt user@sunfire.comp.nus.edu.sg:/tmp/temp/. 

You'll be prompted for your password.
Once transfer is done, you need to modify the file permission, so others
could access it.

(Let's just give all permission)

chmod 777 <your file>

And you are done.
###############################################





##############################################
To copy files from here to your computer:

    scp <your unix id>@sunfire.comp.nus.edu.sg:/tmp/temp/<path to file>
        <path to where you want to save your file>
Eg.
    scp user@sunfire.comp.nus.edu.sg:/tmp/temp/README.txt ~/Downloads/.

You'll be prompted for your password.
Wait for transfer to be completed, and you're done.
#############################################
